radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis; Two subcentimeter hypodense liver lesions within segments II and V likely represent liver cysts or hemangiomas; Normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands; Small hiatal hernia; Cecal wall thickening and pericecal fat stranding; Approximately 2 cm tubular structure along lateral wall of the cecum likely represents a perforated diverticulum; Normal air-filled appendix; No suspicious focal lesions in kidneys; Tiny fat-containing umbilical hernia.
